'''在线猎手'''（Online predator），亦意译作“'''网络猎手'''”或直译为“'''在线（网络）掠食者'''”，是指出于性或其它虐待之目的而利用脆弱的儿童或青少年的已成年网络使用者。<ref name="myths">{{cite journal |last= Wolak |first= Janis |authorlink=  |coauthors= David Finkelhor, Kimberly J. Mitchell, Michele L. Ybarra |title= Online "predators" and their victims: Myths, realities, and implications for prevention and treatment |journal= [[American_Psychologist|American Psychologist]] |volume= 63 |issue= 2 |pages= 111–128 |id=  |url= http://www.unh.edu/news/cj_nr/2008/feb/lw18internet.cfm |accessdate= 2008-04-21 |quote=  |doi= 10.1037/0003-066X.63.2.111 |pmid= 18284279 |date= Feb–Mar 2008 |archive-date= 2008-03-19 |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20080319001623/http://www.unh.edu/news/cj_nr/2008/feb/lw18internet.cfm |dead-url= no }}</ref>

网络上未成年人受害会包括[[儿童性诱拐|儿童性诱拐]]、[[人类性行为#法律議題|被成人要求性行为]]或性讨论、接收到不想要的[[色情|色情]]物质（如含有裸照的邮件等等），以及网上骚扰、威胁和其它不具有“自然‘性’”（not sexual in nature）却带来沮丧、恐惧和尴尬的冒犯性交流。<ref>"Snyder,H; Sickmund,M: Juvenile Offenders and Victims: 2006 National Report", p38. National Center for Juvenile Justice, March 2006.</ref>

[[聊天室|聊天室]]、[[即时通讯|即时通讯]]、[[讨坛|讨坛]]、[[社交服务|社交服务]]，甚或是[[电子游乐器|电子游乐器]]都因招来在线猎手而受人诟病。而据2007年的一份研究显示，没有发现一例通过上传个人基本资料在社交网站而成为猎手目标的例子。<ref>"Online Predators: Help minimize the risk". Microsoft Corporation . 24 September 2008 <http://www.Microsoft.com/protect/family/guidelines/predators.mspx {{Wayback|url=http://www.microsoft.com/protect/family/guidelines/predators.mspx |date=20100824220824 }}>.</ref><ref>{{cite web| last = Williams| first = Pete| authorlink = Pete Williams| coauthors = | title = MySpace, Facebook attract online predators| work = | publisher = [[MSNBC|MSNBC]]| date = 2006-02-03| url = http://www.msnbc.msn.com/id/11165576/| format = | doi = | accessdate = 2006-12-08| archive-date = 2010-02-08| archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20100208225651/http://www.msnbc.msn.com/id/11165576/| dead-url = no}}</ref><ref>{{cite web| last = Burt| first = David| authorlink = David Burt (filtering advocate)| coauthors = | title = Playstation Pedophiles| work = | publisher = Filtering Facts| date = 2009-03-16| url = http://filteringfacts.org/2009/03/16/playstation-pedophiles/| format = | doi = | accessdate = 2009-03-16| quote = [G]aming consoles such as PlayStation, Wii, and Xbox have become Internet-enabled, interactive devices.  This provides  an opportunity for pedophiles to befriend and groom minors.| deadurl = yes| archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20090405143950/http://filteringfacts.org/2009/03/16/playstation-pedophiles/| archivedate = 2009-04-05}}</ref><ref name="myths"/>

